  "timestamps": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start": 0.15,
      "end": 2.691,
      "text": "You just landed in Canada, now what?",
      "slide_index": 0
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start": 2.991,
      "end": 6.9,
      "text": "Before you get a job, open a bank account, or file taxes.",
      "slide_index": 0
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start": 7.2,
      "end": 8.589,
      "text": "You need one number.",
      "slide_index": 0
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start": 8.889,
      "end": 10.135,
      "text": "It's 9 digits.",
      "slide_index": 0
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start": 10.435,
      "end": 13.072,
      "text": "Without it, you're invisible to the system.",
      "slide_index": 0
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start": 13.872,
      "end": 16.453,
      "text": "SIN stands for Social Insurance Number.",
      "slide_index": 1
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start": 16.753,
      "end": 19.634,
      "text": "Think of it as your economic identity in Canada.",
      "slide_index": 1
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start": 19.934,
      "end": 22.982,
      "text": "Without it, the government doesn't know you exist.",
      "slide_index": 1
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start": 23.782,
      "end": 26.42,
      "text": "Here's what you can't do without a SIN.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start": 26.72,
      "end": 28.276,
      "text": "Number one, work.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start": 28.576,
      "end": 31.471,
      "text": "Your employer literally cannot pay you without it.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start": 31.771,
      "end": 33.546,
      "text": "Number two, taxes.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start": 33.846,
      "end": 37.72,
      "text": "No SIN means no tax return, and you lose your refund.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start": 38.02,
      "end": 39.889,
      "text": "Number three, benefits.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start": 40.189,
      "end": 43.286,
      "text": "Employment insurance, student loans, pension.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start": 43.586,
      "end": 45.439,
      "text": "All tied to your SIN.",
      "slide_index": 2
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start": 46.239,
      "end": 48.996,
      "text": "Getting a SIN is easy, three ways to do it.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start": 49.296,
      "end": 52.6,
      "text": "Fastest option, walk into a Service Canada office.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start": 52.9,
      "end": 54.815,
      "text": "You get your number the same day.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start": 55.115,
      "end": 59.229,
      "text": "Pro tip, most universities invite Service Canada to campus.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start": 59.529,
      "end": 61.884,
      "text": "That happens during orientation week.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start": 62.184,
      "end": 64.085,
      "text": "You can also apply online.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start": 64.385,
      "end": 66.025,
      "text": "Takes a few business days.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start": 66.325,
      "end": 68.98,
      "text": "One thing to watch if you're on a study permit.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start": 69.28,
      "end": 71.079,
      "text": "It must say may work on it.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start": 71.379,
      "end": 74.322,
      "text": "If those words aren't there, check your permit first.",
      "slide_index": 3
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start": 75.122,
      "end": 77.554,
      "text": "Two traps every student needs to know.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start": 77.854,
      "end": 81.57,
      "text": "First, if your SIN starts with 9, it has an expiry date.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start": 81.87,
      "end": 85.136,
      "text": "It expires when your study or work permit expires.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start": 85.436,
      "end": 86.816,
      "text": "Renewed your permit?",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start": 87.116,
      "end": 89.544,
      "text": "You must also update your SIN.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start": 89.844,
      "end": 92.496,
      "text": "Otherwise your employer can't keep paying you.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start": 92.796,
      "end": 95.52,
      "text": "Second, your SIN is not an ID card.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start": 95.82,
      "end": 97.767,
      "text": "Do not give it to just anyone.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start": 98.067,
      "end": 102.765,
      "text": "Your landlord asks for your SIN? You can say no.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start": 103.065,
      "end": 104.561,
      "text": "That's your legal right.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start": 104.861,
      "end": 108.62,
      "text": "You only give it to your employer, your bank, and for taxes.",
      "slide_index": 4
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start": 109.42,
      "end": 112.546,
      "text": "All data comes from the Government of Canada website.",
      "slide_index": 5
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start": 112.846,
      "end": 114.366,
      "text": "Links are on screen.",
      "slide_index": 5
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start": 115.166,
      "end": 116.711,
      "text": "Follow for part two.",
      "slide_index": 6
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start": 117.011,
      "end": 120.287,
      "text": "Which Canadian bank is actually free for newcomers?",
      "slide_index": 6
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start": 120.587,
      "end": 122.828,
      "text": "I compared all five big banks.",
      "slide_index": 6
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start": 123.128,
      "end": 125.599,
      "text": "The difference is a full year of free banking.",
      "slide_index": 6
    }
  ],
